SUPER Eagles midfielder, John Ogu has announced the arrival of his new baby. Ogu made the announcement via his official Twitter account and said the mother is doing fine. The Hapoel Nof HaGhalil midfielder is being congratulated by fans of the Super Eagles and his followers for the latest addition to his family.   Qatar 2022 WC Draw: Senegal up against Netherlands, Ghana…     Deschamps wary of Denmark threat     I’m honoured to be featured in World Cup theme song, Davido   Ogu is one of Nigeria’s most adored players as a result of his strong fan engagement and relationship. The midfielder last represented the Super Eagles at the 2019 AFCON where he won a bronze medal for the team. Ogu was also at the 2018 World Cup and had played in the 2013 Confederations Cup for the Super Eagles. The midfielder didn’t reveal the gender of the baby.